<h3>MCABBER</h3>
<h4>Introdution</h4>
<tt>mcabber</tt> is a small Jabber console client.<br/>
<tt>mcabber</tt> includes features such as <b>SASL/SSL/TLS</b> support, <b>MUC</b>
(Multi-User Chat) support, <b>history</b> logging, <b>command completion</b>,
Open<b>PGP</b> encryption, <b>OTR</b> (Off-the-Record Messaging) support,
<b>dynamic modules</b> and <b>external action</b> triggers.<br/>
Please read the manual page (manpage link below) for more information.<br/>
<br/>
<tt>mcabber</tt> is released under the GNU GPL, and has been tested on
GNU/Linux, BSD, Mac OS X and Cygwin.<br/>

<h4>News</h4>
<ul>
  <li><b>2010/12/01: <tt>mcabber 0.10.1</tt> released.</b>
      <font size=-1>Bugfix release.
      See the <a href="files/ChangeLog">changelog file</a> or the repository
      for details.</font>
  <li><b>2010/05/24: Google <em>Summer of Code.</em></b>
      <font size=-1>
      Nicolas (a.k.a. alkino) is working on <em>Jingle file transfer</em>
      modules for mcabber.  See his <a href="http://gsoc-mcabber.blogspot.com/">blog</a>.
      Please check the wiki for the Jingle modules!</font>
  <li><b>2010/04/11: <tt>mcabber 0.10.0</tt> released.</b>
      <font size=-1>Switch to the Loudmouth library, support for dynamic
      modules, and much more.  See the <a href="files/ChangeLog">changelog file</a>
      for a list of changes.  Do not forget to update your configuration file
      before starting the new version :)<br/>
      Please see the
      <a href="http://wiki.mcabber.com/index.php/Modules">module wiki</a>
      page as well!<br/>
      Your can try our
      <a href="http://mcabber.com/files/loudmouth-1.4.3+gitb5a9de5b.20100413.tar.bz2">
      loudmouth version</a>, since we have applied some
      <a href="http://github.com/mcabber/loudmouth/commits/master">patches</a>.
      </font>
  <li><b>2010/04/06: <tt>mcabber 0.10.0-rc5</tt> released.</b>
      <font size=-1>5th Release Candidate for 0.10.0.</font>
  <li><b>2010/04/04: <tt>mcabber 0.10.0-rc3</tt> released.</b>
      <font size=-1>3rd Release Candidate for 0.10.0.</font>
  <li><b>2010/03/28: <tt>mcabber 0.10.0-rc2</tt> released.</b>
      <font size=-1>Release Candidate for 0.10.0.  MCabber now uses the
      Loudmouth XMPP library, and has support for dynamic module
      loading/unloading.</font>
  <li><b>2009/10/06: <tt>mcabber 0.9.10</tt> released.</b>
      <font size=-1>Support for spell checking with Enchant, many bugfixes
      and improvements.  Please note that spellchecking-related options
      have changed a little in the configuration file.</font>
  <li><b>2008/10/11: New user guide.</b> <font size=-1>See the links below
      for franky's mcabber user guide!</font>
  <li><b>2008/10/09: <tt>mcabber 0.9.9</tt> released.</b>
      <font size=-1>A few bugfixes, help translation updates and new
      Czech translation.</font>
  <li><b>2008/10/05: <tt>mcabber 0.9.8</tt> released.</b>
      <font size=-1>URLs can be extracted from messages to the log window
      with the new url_regex option, OTR messages are now displayed with
      "O" flag, a few new commands and options are available, as well as
      several UI improvements.</font>
  <li><b>2008/04/17: <tt>mcabber 0.9.7</tt> released.</b>
      <font size=-1>FIFO support, new external event ("unread"), a few new
       options, and a lots of small fixes and improvements.</font>
  <li><b>2008/01/13: <tt>mcabber 0.9.6</tt> released.</b>
      <font size=-1>(Bugfix release) Better Cygwin support, better OpenBSD
      support, misc. small improvements and bugfixes.</font>
  <li><b>2007/11/19: <tt>mcabber 0.9.5</tt> released.</b>
      <font size=-1>Internal hooks, improved command /source,
      removed UI restriction on the message size, misc. improvements and
      bugfixes.</font>
  <li><b>2007/10/27: <tt>mcabber 0.9.4</tt> released.</b>
      <font size=-1>GnuTLS support, OTR (Off-The-Record) support, improved
      user interface with MUC nickname coloring and selectable time prefixes,
      misc. improvements and bugfixes.</font>
  <li><b>2007/06/19: <tt>mcabber 0.9.3</tt> released.</b>
      <font size=-1>(Bugfix release)</font>
</ul>

