<h4>Packages</h4>
Please see the wiki for a list of
<a href="http://wiki.mcabber.com/index.php/Packages">known
MCabber packages</a> for your operating system.

<h4>Support, Development</h4>
MCabber is maintained by Mikael BERTHE.<br/>
There is currently no mailing list about <tt>mcabber</tt>.  You can join the
MCabber MUC conference room if you have some suggestions or questions:
<em>mcabber@conf.lilotux.net</em>.<br/>
There are a
<a href="http://wiki.mcabber.com/index.php/Frequently_Asked_Questions">FAQ</a>
and a
<a href="http://wiki.mcabber.com/index.php/Mcabber_Wiki:Community_Portal">Community Portal</a>
on the wiki.<br/>
You can report bugs or add suggestions to the
<a href="http://www.bitbucket.org/McKael/mcabber-crew/issues/?status=new&status=open">
Bitbucket Issue Tracker</a>.<br/>
<br/>
New versions are announced on the
<a href="http://freshmeat.net/projects/mcabber/">freshmeat</a>
website, and you can subscribe to new releases on the freshmeat page to be
notified when a new <tt>mcabber</tt> version is out.
<br/><br/>

If you are interested in <tt>mcabber</tt> development, please have a look at
the <a href="http://mcabber.com/hg/">Mercurial</a> repository.  You can join the MCabber MUC
conference room too (see above).
<br/>

